title: Seattle Thunderbirds win 3-2 in shootout over Prince Albert
text:
Seattle Thunderbirds win 3-2 in shootout over Prince Albert Originally published October 10, 2015 at 9:58 pm Updated October 10, 2015 at 9:59 pm Seattle’s Mathew Barzal, Jamal Watson and Keegan Kolesar all scored shootout goals. By Seattle Times staff The Seattle Times 
Mathew Barzal, Jamal Watson and Keegan Kolesar all scored in a shootout as the Seattle Thunderbirds earned a 3-2 victory over visiting Prince Albert on Saturday. 
Barzal and Kolesar also had power-play goals for Seattle. 
The T-birds outshot the Raiders 40-20. At Everett 5, Spokane 4 (OT) 
Remi Laurencelle scored his second goal of the game 2:08 into overtime to lift the Silvertips past the Chiefs. Most Read Stories
